# Homepage Docs files

- Source of truth for the **Docs** tab: `public/docs/*.md`
- Nav order: `public/docs/manifest.json` (`pages[].id`, `title`, `file`)
- Left sidebar subjects are built from `manifest.json`
- Renderer: `public/markdown.js` — demos reuse **real app CSS classes**

## Cross-links

Use `[Label](doc:page-id)` (e.g. `[Market](doc:market)`).

App routes: `/` (main/app), `/docs` (documentation), `/version` (release notes).

## Visual references (must match the app)

Fenced `demo` blocks are non-interactive but must use the same markup/classes as the live UI:

````md
```demo
trade-toggle|Allow trade|off
trade-toggle|Auto Trade|on
trade-size|10|shares
trade-toggle|Use Schedule|on
modal-toggle|Optimize|off
modal-input|Shares to buy|10
modal-select|Gap vs PTB|with|None=none,Opposite=opposite,With=with
modal-stack|Title|My setup
page-toggle|Schedule|Heatmap|Schedule
auth-buttons|Log in|Sign up
```
````

| Demo type | Matches |
|-----------|---------|
| `trade-toggle` / `trade-size` | Market Trade panel (`.wallet-control-field`) |
| `modal-toggle` / `modal-input` / `modal-select` / `modal-stack` | Phase / setup modals |
| `settings-field` | Settings page inputs |
| `page-toggle` | Header Schedule / Heatmap toggle |
| `auth-buttons` | Main Log in / Sign up |

## Flow diagrams

Fenced `flow` blocks render simple container → arrow rows:

````md
```flow
# Title
Browser -> REST /api -> Server
Server -> SSE /api/stream -> Browser
```
````

Keep flows minimal (few boxes). Channel names like REST/SSE/WS get accent styling.
